*VERY GOOD NEIGHBORHOOD BAR*  Hi Guys, its me Robert the Elevator Guy Again. I was looking for a nice place to have lunch break. On duty w/my partner after fixing 3 elevators. Was going to go to "The Grange" (Google suggested). But ended at "The Grill on the Hill", glad I did. Which is located across from The Grange. Grange looked a little stuffy n no TV. The Grill is about 600sf in the front. I didnt go to the back where the Pool Table & Games were. The front room had 7 TVs. Which I appreciated, Round 2 March Madness was on. I did like the long picnic table in the middle. Extended for about 20'.  The Food was very good. Regular bar food. I had a burger, maybe 7oz after cooking.  Fries tasted as if from fresh cut potato n were piping hot. But it was already salted, a No No. I had asked for cole slaw, didnt  get it. They said they were out, another demerit. They did have 16 draft beers. Perfectly chilled. My server was Dave, A cool guy.

Tried this place out last night and my order arrived 30 minutes after the expected time. I tried calling the restaurant but they proceeded to pick up and quickly hang up. In response, I called seamless/GrubHub, and they told me the delivery guy was on his way even though my order was marked as delivered around 20 minutes before I called. After arriving the delivery guy decided to try to have a conversation explaining that I was at fault because I did not pick up the phone meanwhile I had no missed calls and I had literally just seen him dial my phone number. I thought hey besides hanging up the place isn't at fault, so I just ate my food. I saw that the $10 fries were very few and as I bit into my jumbo wings the meat was still raw! This place was definitely not worth it, it is overpriced and not worth the money, I would recommend skipping this place.
